# Superpowers Workflow

**Before any feature or behavior change**, follow this order. Skills in `.agents/skills/` from [obra/superpowers](https://skills.sh/obra/superpowers).

## Skill order

| Phase | Skill | When |
|-------|-------|------|
| 1 | `using-superpowers` | Start of every task — check applicable skills |
| 2 | `brainstorming` | New features, non-trivial changes — **design before code** |
| 3 | `writing-plans` | After approved design — implementation plan |
| 4 | `test-driven-development` | During implementation — tests with code |
| 5 | `executing-plans` | Multi-step plans in batches |
| 6 | `verification-before-completion` | Before claiming done — run tests, show output |

## Hard gates

- **No implementation** until brainstorming design is approved (can be brief for tiny fixes).
- **No "done"** without running relevant tests (`make test-backend` / `make test-frontend`).
- Invoke skills proactively — if a skill might apply (even 1%), use it.

## Quick vs full workflow

| Change size | Workflow |
|-------------|----------|
| Typo, comment, config only | Skip brainstorming; still run affected tests if any |
| Bug fix | `systematic-debugging` → fix → add regression test |
| New endpoint / page / migration | Full: brainstorm → plan → TDD → verify |
| Refactor | Plan → keep tests green → verify |

## Project skills

- `nurul-hikmah-stack` — feature checklist
- `laravel-development` — backend patterns (repository + cache)
- `security-audit` — auth / OWASP changes

